The paper deals with object tracking using event-based vision sensors, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a novel approach to utilizing the temporal component of the event stream, which involves the development of new algorithms, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE).
